race.comment: CASHOUT (1) looks the one to beat. He debuted at Seymour over 1300m and hit the line sweetly after drawing widest, beaten just 1.2 lengths when finishing third. He gets the golden switch here to barrier four, should relish the slight rise in trip and should improve off the debut. UPOLU (7) has just found one better both times he's stepped out. Both efforts have been very good and he maps for every chance here. SUPERGRACE (12) was okay first up at Mornington, beaten 3.5 lengths. She showed a bit of promise in her maiden campaign and can be an improver at odds here. STELLETTA (11) has been much better her past couple and a maiden win looks close. She is back sharply in trip off a let up here which is the knock but expect she's strong late.
